    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1333"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/292</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Petrograd</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-10">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7:06 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>9. Russian Government is still waiting England’s action concerning Red Cross ship
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamburg</hi>. Papers report that ship detained at request
                    British Ambassador, Washington, as most of crew discovered to be Germans.
                    Request from beginning has caused bad impression at Foreign Office and in
                    press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
